Did something happen?

615
00:46:04,365 --> 00:46:05,896
Oh, it's nothing.

616
00:46:06,825 --> 00:46:09,196
Did you have a good time with your mother?

617
00:46:10,836 --> 00:46:11,836
Yes.

618
00:46:12,966 --> 00:46:14,135
Why are you holding that?

619
00:46:16,276 --> 00:46:17,845
I think I can figure it out.

620
00:46:18,276 --> 00:46:20,515
- Figure what out? - The guy with the blue cap.

621
00:46:21,345 --> 00:46:22,416
The answer...

622
00:46:23,446 --> 00:46:24,986
might be in this manuscript.

623
00:46:37,466 --> 00:46:39,225
A novel is not a report.

624
00:46:41,336 --> 00:46:43,434
Although it was based on a true story,

625
00:46:43,435 --> 00:46:45,836
that doesn't mean actual names were used.

626
00:46:46,836 --> 00:46:48,235
At first,

627
00:46:48,236 --> 00:46:50,405
I thought Ko Mi Sook didn't write about a person with a blue cap.

628
00:46:51,546 --> 00:46:54,075
But then I remembered that there was a similar line.

629
00:46:55,975 --> 00:46:57,446
"A blue-headed man."

630
00:46:59,015 --> 00:47:01,015
This whole time,

631
00:47:01,885 --> 00:47:03,955
I thought that meant that he had blue hair.

632
00:47:09,526 --> 00:47:11,296
What on earth happened?

633
00:47:12,796 --> 00:47:14,896
Do I have to tell you everything?

634
00:47:16,336 --> 00:47:19,865
Do I have to share every tiny detail of everything that happens here?

635
00:47:20,205 --> 00:47:21,475
Are you?

636
00:47:22,376 --> 00:47:24,606
Were we even that close?

637
00:47:34,716 --> 00:47:35,856
You know, don't you?

638
00:47:40,325 --> 00:47:41,426
The blue cap.

639
00:47:43,696 --> 00:47:45,325
You're not even curious.

640
00:47:48,666 --> 00:47:50,135
You found out who it is, right?

641
00:47:51,765 --> 00:47:53,606
You didn't miss him at the teahouse.

642
00:47:58,245 --> 00:47:59,676
You don't need to tell me,

643
00:47:59,975 --> 00:48:01,614
but isn't there also no reason for you to hide it from me?

644
00:48:01,615 --> 00:48:03,445
Why? What is it?

645
00:48:03,446 --> 00:48:05,745
I think you're misunderstanding something.

646
00:48:06,745 --> 00:48:07,955
Think carefully.

647
00:48:08,885 --> 00:48:11,025
If I really came here for coverage purposes,

648
00:48:11,026 --> 00:48:13,756
why would I go out of my way to catch the criminal?

649
00:48:15,455 --> 00:48:16,995
Because I feel bad for the victims?

650
00:48:18,126 --> 00:48:20,126
This world is full of such tragedies.

651
00:48:20,796 --> 00:48:23,836
I don't have enough time on my hands to save all those people.

652
00:48:25,765 --> 00:48:26,935
Then what's the reason?

653
00:48:31,245 --> 00:48:32,606
I am also a victim.

654
00:48:33,776 --> 00:48:35,075
The fifth victim.

655
00:48:38,345 --> 00:48:40,455
I end up dying in the future, just like your mother,

656
00:48:41,216 --> 00:48:43,416
because the culprit was not caught properly.

657
00:48:44,126 --> 00:48:46,256
I came here to save my own life.

658
00:48:46,356 --> 00:48:49,925
I input every newspaper story, news broadcast, and case file...

659
00:48:49,926 --> 00:48:51,965
related to this village in 1987...

660
00:48:51,966 --> 00:48:53,526
into my head.

661
00:48:54,365 --> 00:48:57,205
But everything might go down the drain because of one variable.

662
00:48:58,805 --> 00:49:01,435
That alone makes me feel like my head is going to explode.

663
00:49:03,876 --> 00:49:05,106
But you know what?

664
00:49:07,615 --> 00:49:09,975
Do you know who the biggest variable is?

665
00:49:12,986 --> 00:49:15,555
Is that why you sent me to my mom last night?

666
00:49:18,586 --> 00:49:21,126
"Don't even be curious about the variables."

667
00:49:22,896 --> 00:49:24,225
"Don't get in the way."

668
00:49:25,365 --> 00:49:26,466
"Stay out of this."

669
00:49:28,566 --> 00:49:30,095
Is that what you want to say?

670
00:49:34,736 --> 00:49:36,506
I'm sorry, but I can't do that.

671
00:49:38,176 --> 00:49:39,676
Since I've already come this far,

672
00:49:40,845 --> 00:49:43,015
I don't want to sit on my hands like an idiot.

673
00:49:46,015 --> 00:49:47,486
If you don't want to tell me, suit yourself.

674
00:49:49,216 --> 00:49:50,756
I'm going to find out myself.

675
00:50:04,066 --> 00:50:05,736
I feel so uncomfortable.

676
00:50:08,475 --> 00:50:10,546
What if Bum Ryong cries and becomes clingy?

677
00:50:11,745 --> 00:50:13,946
He said he only had me in his life.

678
00:50:16,615 --> 00:50:17,745
What are you doing?

679
00:50:19,086 --> 00:50:20,345
Hey, Baek Yoon Young.

680
00:50:27,325 --> 00:50:30,225
"On the afternoon that the first victim's corpse was found,"

681
00:50:31,396 --> 00:50:34,635
"there were a few people who started acting strange."

682
00:50:35,935 --> 00:50:37,565
"The blue-headed man..."

683
00:50:37,566 --> 00:50:40,006
"stood between the sun and the moon for what seemed like forever."

684
00:50:41,035 --> 00:50:42,635
"The man with glasses..."

685
00:50:43,236 --> 00:50:45,975
"was not able to come out of the third stall for a long time."

686
00:50:47,146 --> 00:50:48,776
"The man who had lost his memory..."

687
00:50:49,376 --> 00:50:52,185
"lay down under the bridge, not realizing who he was."

688
00:50:54,216 --> 00:50:56,715
(The blue-headed man stood between the sun...)

689
00:50:56,716 --> 00:50:59,086
(and the moon for what seemed like forever.)

690
00:51:00,126 --> 00:51:02,725
Lee Ju Young was found dead today.

691
00:51:04,225 --> 00:51:05,966
So this is talking about this afternoon.

692
00:51:07,495 --> 00:51:11,236
If "the blue-headed man" really means a man in a blue hat...

693
00:51:11,836 --> 00:51:15,336
(The sun and the moon)

694
00:51:16,006 --> 00:51:17,845
where could "between the sun and the moon" be?

695
00:51:18,946 --> 00:51:19,946
I don't know.

696
00:51:20,845 --> 00:51:23,276
What is that? It's scaring me.

697
00:51:26,946 --> 00:51:28,785
Just go and meet Yoo Bum Ryong.

698
00:51:29,916 --> 00:51:31,825
You have to deal with it one way or another.

699
00:51:33,825 --> 00:51:35,225
Fine, I will.

700
00:51:39,626 --> 00:51:42,135
By the way, don't hang out with whoever wrote that.

701
00:51:46,535 --> 00:51:47,676
I don't like it.

702
00:51:48,006 --> 00:51:49,975
How did you know it wasn't me who wrote it?

703
00:51:50,376 --> 00:51:51,446
Are you stupid?

704
00:51:52,075 --> 00:51:53,075
There's no way...

705
00:51:53,076 --> 00:51:54,245
you wouldn't understand something you wrote yourself.

706
00:51:54,615 --> 00:51:55,975
The writer should know everything...

707
00:51:56,515 --> 00:51:58,546
because they chose each word carefully.

708
00:52:02,916 --> 00:52:03,955
See you.

709
00:52:17,935 --> 00:52:20,405
She wouldn't know something she wrote 30 years from now.

710
00:53:25,236 --> 00:53:26,236
Hae Jun!

711
00:53:27,236 --> 00:53:29,704
- Hae Jun! - What in the world?

712
00:53:29,705 --> 00:53:30,776
Hey.

