721
00:55:26,185 --> 00:55:28,896
"A man stood between the sun and the moon for what seemed like forever."

722
00:55:35,635 --> 00:55:37,396
If a sentence like this exists,

723
00:55:38,506 --> 00:55:40,805
what could "between the sun and the moon" mean?

724
00:55:48,075 --> 00:55:49,446
How am I supposed to know?

725
00:55:57,586 --> 00:55:58,856
I shouldn't have asked her.

726
00:56:01,256 --> 00:56:02,896
Isn't that the name of the record shop?

727
00:56:14,166 --> 00:56:16,475
(Sun and Moon Record Shop)

728
00:56:17,845 --> 00:56:19,344
(Sun)

729
00:56:19,345 --> 00:56:21,345
(Guitar lessons)

730
00:57:06,185 --> 00:57:10,225
(Sun and Moon Record Shop)

731
00:57:52,606 --> 00:57:54,676
Do you know what time it is right now?

732
00:57:59,805 --> 00:58:00,845
Then...

733
00:58:01,515 --> 00:58:03,215
do you know how it feels to wait for someone...

734
00:58:03,216 --> 00:58:04,845
after hearing that they left school early?

735
00:58:07,015 --> 00:58:08,755
Because we're living in this stupid year 1987,

736
00:58:08,756 --> 00:58:10,655
I couldn't even call you.

737
00:58:17,966 --> 00:58:18,995
I'm sorry.

738
00:58:21,466 --> 00:58:23,195
I knew I should've told you,

739
00:58:23,196 --> 00:58:25,066
but I hid the truth from you.

740
00:58:26,435 --> 00:58:28,935
But I didn't send you to your mom to get rid of you or anything.

741
00:58:30,905 --> 00:58:31,975
I know.

742
00:58:35,316 --> 00:58:37,614
The man with the blue cap is your...

743
00:58:37,615 --> 00:58:38,845
I know that as well.

744
00:58:42,356 --> 00:58:43,856
I saw him with my own eyes.

745
00:58:45,256 --> 00:58:47,154
I also think I know why you had no choice...

746
00:58:47,155 --> 00:58:48,825
but to hide the truth from me.

747
00:58:51,095 --> 00:58:52,225
Because we're family.

748
00:58:54,765 --> 00:58:56,595
He's just one of the suspects.

749
00:59:01,836 --> 00:59:03,106
I never really liked him,

750
00:59:04,575 --> 00:59:07,446
but I also never expected him to be so cruel.

751
00:59:09,146 --> 00:59:11,986
My father loves him to bits.

752
00:59:14,816 --> 00:59:15,856
Even more than he loves us.

753
00:59:19,185 --> 00:59:20,285
What?

754
00:59:22,796 --> 00:59:23,796
Sorry?

755
00:59:24,396 --> 00:59:25,396
I mean...

756
00:59:27,265 --> 00:59:29,336
Who are you talking about right now?

757
00:59:29,935 --> 00:59:32,534
I thought we were talking about the man with the blue cap.

758
00:59:32,535 --> 00:59:33,566
Exactly.

759
00:59:34,305 --> 00:59:37,876
Why does Baek Hee Sub love himself to bits?

760
00:59:41,075 --> 00:59:44,046
Are you saying the man with the blue cap is my father?

761
00:59:48,455 --> 00:59:49,955
Then who did you see?

762
00:59:52,526 --> 00:59:54,995
(Sun and Moon Record Shop)

763
01:00:25,555 --> 01:00:26,926
My uncle.

764
01:00:28,296 --> 01:00:29,296
Baek Yu Sub.

765
01:00:30,655 --> 01:00:32,595
Baek Yu Sub wasn't even a suspect,

766
01:00:33,296 --> 01:00:35,495
and he wasn't in the vicinity last night.

767
01:00:51,416 --> 01:00:53,015
Everything makes sense now.

768
01:01:07,526 --> 01:01:08,665
